f
ighter and in both capacities he operated in the areas that are today North-Central Greece, Southwestern Bulgaria and the Republic of Macedonia. He felt equally comfortable in all three regions. He was shot to death by the Turks in Banitsa, then a Bulgari
an village, today, a Greek one. It was in a spring day in May 1903. 
\par The death of this sad but steely eyed, heavily moustached youth 
