ingly and virulently nationalistic Croatia. The Hungarians used this to their advantage by fanning Croat-Serb hostility. After all, they had a historical account to settle with the Serbs who quashed an Hungarian rebellion not 40 years before (in 1848-9) a
nd were awarded with the half autonomous Duchy of Vojvodina, an integral part of the Kingdom of Hungary. 
